# Sajtmaskin context skill routing

Use `.cursor/skills/sajtmaskin-context/SKILL.md` as the first context layer for domain-relevant tasks.

## Trigger scenarios

Apply the skill when the task mentions or implies:

- Builder flow, build methods, build intent, prompt modes
- Template gallery vs scaffold vs Vercel template distinctions
- Project/chat/version concepts, demoUrl, preview, deployment flow
- Runtime lane vs research lane generation architecture
- Platform behavior or docs for `v0`, `Vercel`, OpenAI APIs, or OpenClaw

## Coordination notes

- Keep canonical terminology from `.cursor/rules/terminology.mdc`.
- Keep MCP routing defaults from `.cursor/rules/mcp-docs-routing.mdc`.
- For React/Next/Node/performance implementation tasks, also apply `vercel-react-best-practices`.
- For generic non-domain coding tasks, `sajtmaskin-context` may be skipped.
